  <!-- 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Type: shape_model_element 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
   -->
    <ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.shape_model_element">
 	 A <b>shape_model_element</b> is a select type used to specify the types of
 <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/> 
 used to define constructional operations in a 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation"/> .

 	 
  </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_shape_representation
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation">
 A <b>Procedural_shape_representation</b> is a  type of 
 <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>
  that represents the shape in terms of a set of 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence"/>s.



</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_shape_representation Attribute SELF\Representation.items
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation.items">
 <p>the set of sequences of operations used to create the shape being represented.
<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note>
</p>

</ext_description>








<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_shape_representation_sequence 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence">
<p> A <b>Procedural_shape_representation_sequence</b> is a  type of 
<express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>
that specifies a sequence of shape modification operations to create a 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation"/>. It is used to represent the construction history of a 
procedural solid model.

<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note> </p>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_shape_representation_sequence Attribute elements
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.elements">
 the sequential list of 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.shape_model_element"/>
defining the operations to be performed by the receiving system in order to re-create the intended shape model.
 </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_shape_representation_sequence Attribute suppressed_elements
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.suppressed_elements">
 the set of 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.shape_model_element"/>
defining the operations which may be omitted by the the receiving system in order to create 
a simplified version of the intended shape model.
 </ext_description>




<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Procedural_shape_representation_sequence Attribute rationale
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.rationale">
 the description of the reasons for using an instance of this entity.
</ext_description>


<!-- WR1 -->
 <ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.wr:WR1">
 No element shall be included in the 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.suppressed_elements"/>
 set that is not in the list of 
 <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Procedural_shape_representation_sequence.elements"/>.
 </ext_description>




<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship">
<p> An <b>Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship</b> is a  type of 
 <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_relationship"/>
that relates a procedural shape model to an explicit model of the same shape that is the current result.

<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note> </p>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship Attribute SELF\Reresentation_relationship.rep_1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship.rep_1">
 the procedural representation of the shape via a sequence of operations.

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship Attribute SELF\Reresentation_relationship.rep_2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship.rep_2">
 the explicit representation of the shape that is the current result of the modelling operations.
 
</ext_description>

<!-- WR1 -->
 <ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship.wr:WR1">
 	The representation <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship.rep_2"/>
 	shall not be a procedurally defined representation.
 	
</ext_description>





<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship">
<p> An <b>Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship</b> is a relationship between two instances of 
<express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>,
one procedurally defined and the other explicitly defined.


<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note> </p>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity:  Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship Attribute  relating_item
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship.relating_item">
 the procedural definition of the geometric element.

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity:  Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship Attribute related_item
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship.related_item">
 the explicit representation of the shape that is the current result of the modelling operations.
 
</ext_description>

<!-- WR1 -->
 <ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_geometric_representation_item_relationship.wr:WR1">
 	The element <express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.Explicit_procedural_shape_representation_relationship.rep_2"/>
 	shall not be procedurally defined.
 	
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: User_selected_shape_elements 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.User_selected_shape_elements">
<p> A <b>User_selected_shape_elements</b> is a  type of 
<express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/>
that provides a reference to one or more 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.shape_model_element"/>s


<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note> </p>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: User_selected_shape_elements  Attribute selected_items
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.User_selected_shape_elements.selected_items">
set of geometric elements that are to be matched with corresponding elements of the explicit shape model regenerated from 
the transferred construction history model.
 </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Indirectly_selected_shape_elements 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Indirectly_selected_shape_elements">
<p> An <b>Indirectly_selected_shape_elements</b> is a  type of 
<express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.User_selected_shape_elements"/>
that provides a reference to an additional set of indirectly selected  
<express_ref linkend="procedural_shape_model:arm:Procedural_shape_model_arm.shape_model_element"/>s


<note> This entity is incompletely modelled in the ARM. Complete specification 
can be obtained in the definition of the corresponding MIM entity.
</note> </p>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Procedural_shape_model_arm  Entity: Indirectly_selected_shape_elements  Attribute indirectly_selected_items
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Procedural_shape_model_arm.Indirectly_selected_shape_elements.indirectly_selected_items">
a set of geometric elements that are to be matched with corresponding elements of the explicit shape model regenerated from 
the transferred construction history model.
 </ext_description>






</ext_descriptions>


